file_description: survey results from follow up 1 and 2
variable_description: How often have you thought about drinking or about how good a drink would make you feel?
response_1: Never - 0 times during this period of time
value_2: Rarely - 1 to 2 times during this period of time
value_3: Occasionally - 3 to 4 times during this period of time
value_4: Sometimes - 5 to 10 times during this period of time
value_5: Often - 11 to 20 times during this period of time
value_6: Most of the time - 20 to 40 times during this period of time
value_7: Nearly all of the time - more than 40 times or more than 6 times per day

file_description: survey results from follow up 1 and 2
variable_description: At its most severe point, how strong was your craving?
value_2: Slight, that is a very mild urge
value_6: Strong urge and difficult to control
value_7: Strong urge and would have drunk alcohol if it were available

variable_description: How much time have you spent thinking about drinking or about how good a drink would make you feel?

file_description: survey results from follow up 1 and 2
variable_description: How difficult would it have been to resist taking a drink if you had known a bottle were in your house?
value_7: Would not be able to resist

file_description: survey results from follow up 1 and 2
variable_description: Keeping in mind your responses to the previous questions, please rate your overall average alcohol craving for the past month.
response_1: Never thought about drinking and never had the urge to drink
value_2: Rarely thought about drinking and rarely had the urge to drink
value_3: Occasionally thought about drinking and occasionally had the urge to drink
value_4: Sometimes thought about drinking and sometimes had the urge to drink
value_5: Often thought about drinking and often had the urge to drink
value_6: Thought about drinking most of the time and had the urge to drink most of the time
value_7: Thought about drinking nearly all of the time and had the urge to drink nearly all of the time
